A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 9 of Chapter 6 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to speed restrictions, so as to provide for a minimum speed limit of 50 miles per hour
3 on certain highways; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
4 purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Article 9 of Chapter 6 of Title 40 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
8 speed restrictions, is amended by revising Code Section 40-6-184, relating to impeding
9 traffic flow, minimum speed limits, and slower driving in a passing lane, as follows:
10 "40-6-184.
11 (a) No person shall drive a motor vehicle at such a slow speed as to impede the normal and
12 reasonable movement of traffic, except when reduced speed is necessary for safe operation.
13 (b) Whenever the commissioner of public safety or the commissioner of transportation or
14 local authorities determine on the basis of any engineering and traffic investigation that
15 slow speeds on any part of a road under their respective jurisdictions impede the normal
16 and reasonable movement of traffic, such commissioners jointly, or such local authorities,
